- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing): The paper discusses reducing computational burden on large power systems, which could involve distributed or parallel computing techniques. 
- cs.PF (Power and Energy): The paper deals with power systems and voltage stability assessment, which falls under the scope of this category. 
- cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing): Although not directly related to neural or evolutionary computing, the paper proposes an adaptive method for improving convergence, which could involve machine learning techniques. 
- cs.ET (Embedded Systems): The paper proposes a method for real-time voltage stability assessment, which could involve embedded systems for monitoring and control.
